Singer Bella Shmurda has recounted his birth story at 25. Shmurda, who rose to prominence after his debut single “Vision 2020” and a follow-up (remix) to the single in which he featured Olamide, tweeted his mother was experiencing hard labour in the course of his birth. He however noted the continuous bleating of a goat at the backyard of the traditional hospital where his mother in Ikorodu, ended up making his birth seamlessly. According to the Dangbana Republik artiste, he eventually arrived in the wee hours of the morning, 3 am precise.   I want the homeless to model my clothes – Kanye West     Feeding only thing on Nigerians’ mind, says Speed…     Whitemoney to hang out with Ojuelegba bridge co-tenants   - Advertisement - “I was born around 3 am in the midnight, my mum said it was so hard for her but there was a goat outside the traditional hospital screaming meeeeeeehhh. “And while it was doing that I was coming out slowly till I was born the goat did not stop screaming at the backyard of the hospital in Ikorodu to be precise Ita Elewa Wera Street,” he tweeted. Revealing his plans for his birthday, the award-winning “Cash App” singer pledged to feed one thousand people in Okoko/Alaba axis. He added: “Anyways, I’m feeding 1k mouths today in my hood Okoko/Alaba and I will be doing it every year by God’s grace he no go shake.”